Sat. V. (717.)

This satire is a humorous relation of a journey to Brundisium. in which Horace accompanied Maecenas, who was employed on the state embassy which negotiated for Angustus the amicable arrangement with Antonius dessign-cited as the treaty of Tarentum (A.U.C. 717). See Men-tuate iii. 197 (Am. ed.)

The student should read this satire with a map of Ancient Italy open before him.
